TEACHERS INSURANCE & ANNUITY ASSOCIATION-COLLEGE RETIREMENT EQUITIES FUND (New York) -- Thomas W. Jones was named executive vice president of finance and planning of this $76 billion pension and insurance system for faculty and staff nationwide.
Mr. Jones, who also becomes chief financial officer, had been senior vice president and treasurer of John Hancock Mutual Life Insurance Co.
He succeeds Thomas G. Walsh, who recently became executive vice president for insurance services. 

